OL,3,CPlans to introduce a four-and-a-half-
OL,4,Cday school week set to be scrapped
OL,6,FHowever, a council report has
OL,7,Frecommended authorities should
OL,8,Fcontinue with the current structure of
OL,9,Fthe school week for primary and
OL,10,Fsecondary schools in Dumfries and
OL,11,FGalloway.
OL,13,FA consultation found that 53% of
OL,14,Fpeople disagree with plans to change
OL,15,Fthe shape of the school week.
OL,17,FThemes against the proposals include
OL,18,Fthe need for more childcare, longer
OL,19,Fdays considered too much for primary
OL,20,Fschool children and the potential
OL,21,Fimpact on poorer families.
